Former Wisconsin sheriff's deputy Andrew Steele, 40, has been found not legally responsible in the killing of his wife and sister-in-law . 
 He shot dead wife Ashlee Steele, 39, and her sister Kacee Tollefsbol, 38, on August 22 . 
 His defense team had argued that Lou Gehrig's disease had damaged his brain, making him not criminally responsible for the deaths . 
 Prosecutors believed Steele had planned the killings abnd a third sister said he had displayed inappropriate feelings towards Tollefsbol . 
 